# Cursor AI Rules for SMILE Project

## AI Documentation System

This project uses an AI-driven documentation system located at `docs/ai-docs/`.

**IMPORTANT**: When modifying code or documentation, follow the AI documentation maintenance rules.

### Quick Start for AI Agents

1. **Read First**: `docs/ai-docs/AI_AGENT_MEMORY.md` - Quick reference guide
2. **Rules**: `docs/ai-docs/RULES.md` - Core maintenance rules
3. **Mapping**: `docs/ai-docs/MAPPING.md` - Document relationships

### When Modifying Documentation

- Always read `docs/ai-docs/RULES.md` before making changes
- Update `docs/ai-docs/INDEX.md` when adding/removing documents
- Update `docs/ai-docs/MAPPING.md` when relationships change
- Run validation: `cd docs/ai-docs && node validate-docs.js`

### Documentation Structure

- `docs/ai-docs/api/` - API endpoint documentation
- `docs/ai-docs/components/` - React component documentation
- `docs/ai-docs/services/` - Service layer documentation
- `docs/ai-docs/features/` - Feature documentation
- `docs/ai-docs/architecture/` - Architecture documentation
- `docs/ai-docs/guides/` - How-to guides

### Key Principles

1. All documents must have YAML frontmatter with metadata
2. All documents must cross-reference related docs
3. Update INDEX.md and MAPPING.md when structure changes
4. Run validation after changes

See `docs/ai-docs/AI_AGENT_MEMORY.md` for complete guide.
